You said:
Oh about that I need some assistancce What factors does the youtube shortz thing depend on? Like tags? or what?
ChatGPT said:

Absolutely, I can help you break down the key factors that contribute to successful YouTube Shorts. Here’s what matters most:

1. Engagement (Watch Time & Retention)

  • Watch Time: YouTube prioritizes Shorts with higher watch time. Even if your video is short, it should engage viewers fully from beginning to end.
  • Retention Rate: You want viewers to watch your video all the way through, and ideally multiple times. A high retention rate (70% and above) can really boost visibility.

2. Video Structure & Hook

  • Immediate Hook: Capture attention in the first 2–3 seconds to prevent viewers from scrolling away.
  • Strong Narrative Flow: Given your preference for emotional storylines, a compelling arc or twist at the end can create a satisfying viewing experience and encourage re-watches.

3. Tags, Titles, and Descriptions

  • Relevant Hashtags: Hashtags like #shorts, #love, #sadstory, or #reunion (depending on your theme) help YouTube categorize your content.
  • Descriptive Title & Keywords: Titles with relevant keywords help YouTube understand the content, which influences who sees your video.
  • Descriptions: While shorter for Shorts, descriptions should be relevant and keyword-rich, helping YouTube’s algorithm with topic matching.

4. Thumbnail (Optional but Useful)

  • Though YouTube Shorts are viewed in a scrollable feed (where thumbnails aren’t prominent), thumbnails still appear in searches and on your channel. For this reason, an appealing thumbnail that conveys the emotion or theme can be a big plus.

5. Audio and Music Selection

  • Trending or emotionally appropriate music can make your Shorts more engaging. If you’re creating a sad or romantic theme, choose sounds that enhance the mood. YouTube’s library has popular sounds, or you can use music relevant to the storyline.

6. Post Timing & Consistency

  • Posting Time: Posting when your target audience is most active can increase visibility. Experiment with different times and analyze your video’s performance.
  • Consistency: Regular uploads build audience familiarity and help with visibility in the algorithm.

7. Engagement Signals (Likes, Shares, Comments)

  • Videos with a high volume of likes, comments, and shares signal to YouTube that people find the content engaging, which boosts your video's reach.

8. Replay Value

  • Content that viewers are likely to rewatch (like a twist ending) will increase your views and boost your Short’s performance. Rewatchability is crucial since YouTube looks at total watch time, especially on loopable Shorts.

Let me know if you want more in-depth insights on any of these points!
